    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Brothers with brothers have not all one heart,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In wrath they turn away and walk apart,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Who from one stream of life had common birth."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What fight for forms! O’er doctrines what vain strife!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Instead together sharing God’s one life,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Who worshipped is by heaven and by earth."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“Where is the truth?” I asked; for this I longed:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "None answered right ’mid all the answering throng;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For ever side by side lay light and shade."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "“Where is,” I cried, “the one communion pure?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Where is the Church in which, clear-traced and sure,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The Spirit’s very likeness is portrayed?”"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So sought I long, and hopeless was my quest;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "These eyes grew dim and blind and found no rest,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Till God’s touch opened them, and I was freed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I found the Spirit’s Church in souls made one"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In this, that they in troth to Christ had come—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "His Bride, to follow where the cross may lead."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thus when I see this small world’s narrow thought,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Behold the brother not with brother brought,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet serving Christ—as each one deemeth right—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Ah, then a voice from realms of glory calls,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Where the last veil is rent and earthward falls,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And where God’s love, eternal, burneth bright."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No more we put that query without end,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To which self-chosen church our feet did trend—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What doctrines we believed, what sacred rites."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In Christ we were in bonds that nought could break;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Who, by His cross and death, do all forsake,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Such as were far asunder He unites."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No longer does one heed mere formal phrase,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Or seek for others’ creeds through winding maze,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For in Himself was truth made manifest."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And out of every tongue and every land"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He formed one Church to meet His own demand—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "His Body, where His fulness is expressed."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    }
  ],
